/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'none'
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()

# Mirrors cire/web's baseline: framing (X-Frame-Options + frame-ancestors),
# MIME-sniffing (nosniff), and referrer protections for the higher-privilege
# organiser portal (OSN access tokens, full guest lists).
#
# Deliberately NO restrictive `script-src`/`connect-src` CSP here: the portal
# talks to two origins (the OSN issuer and cire/api) and loads @osn/ui, and a
# locked-down connect/script policy would break the passkey ceremony and
# authFetch's silent-refresh. A full hardened CSP for the portal is a tracked
# follow-up (S-L1) — see cire/wiki/todo/security.md.
